oach to the Bible still possible? Bringing together essays by eight of today's most prominent philosophers of religion with responses by two leading biblical scholars, Phenomenologies of Scripture reestablishes the possibility of fruitful, dialectical exchange between fields that demand to be read together.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2021) 0aSpinoza, Benedictus de. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Phenomenology.2bisacsh  aBiblical Interpretation.  aBiblical Studies.  aTheological Turn in Phenomenology.  ahermeneutics.  aphenomenology.  aphilosophy of religion.  aphilosophy.  atheology.1 aBloechl, Jeffrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrueggemann, Walter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChrétien, Jean-Louis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHart, Kevin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHorner, Robyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHousset, Emmanuel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLacoste, Jean-Yves, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarion, Jean-Luc, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartin, Dale B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSokolowski, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWells, Adam Y., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWells, Adam Y., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311072900940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823275588zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruy